The once-celebrated union between controversial actress, Nkechi Blessing Sunday and erstwhile husband, Opeyemi Falegan has crashed with both parties blasting each other on Instagram. As the marriage break-up tales continue to flood social media platforms with Nkechi and Falegan throwing caution to the wind and tearing into each other, Tribune Online gathered the marriage may have crashed due to infidelity. Nkechi who took to her Instagram to debunk news flying around that she was dumped by her husband, said she walked away from the union after rumours emerged that her husband walked away from their marriage. While the union, which started in 2021 after Nkechi posted pictures of their traditional marriage on Instagram lasted, she was constantly hyping her man who is based in London. In a video that trended on Instagram Wednesday evening, Falegan who is also a politician claimed that she would not want to be seen with Nkechi whom according to him is notorious for not being ‘faithful’ to him. Nkechi fired back saying she walked away from the marriage for reasons best known to her. The actress also berated the politician on several slides on her Instagram stories. Speaking in the wake of the break-up, Nkechi said she felt relieved to have left her husband using expletive words and insisted that she would not want to remain in a relationship with a man who seemed to be living a fake life and lacked the financial strength to take care of him. “You want to turn me into a bigger (sic) cos of your useless Foundation that you don’t have money to run. Who begs for money to help others? If you no get, go and rest (sic),” she added. The union it was learnt started having issues when Nkechi completed her house in Nigeria as her husband stayed away from the housewarming. The union produced a son.